description: Roman Roads: Paths to Empire History Documentary hosted by David Ackroyd, published by History Channel broadcasted as part of HC In Search of History series in 1997 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/0/0c/Roman-Roads-Paths-to-Empire-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ As the saying goes, "all roads lead to Rome," and they did. Or rather, they lead from Rome. Roman roads were the backbone of the empire, and the paths to glory and greatness. Built to foster conquest and accommodate the Roman army, Roman roads also provided the routes of trade and mercantilism for the empire. This episode of In Search of History examines the roads of the ancient empire and their role in its rise and fall.
